The paper deals with nonparametric hypothesis testing in the context of cognitive radios and wireless sensor networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of universal lossless source codes in the proposed algorithms also suggests a possible connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses a decentralized version of the algorithm, which could indicate a connection to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
